The paper presents a robot that uses deep neural networks for garbage recognition and navigation, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep neural networks for garbage recognition suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel navigation strategy, which involves the use of deep neural networks, indicating artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a possible sub-category. The use of deep learning for both garbage recognition and navigation suggests machine learning (cs.LG) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the autonomous operation of the robot suggests systems and control (cs.SY) as a potential sub-category.
